quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,34,"And We placed therein gardens of palm trees and grapevines and caused to burst forth therefrom some springs -"
  36,35,"That they may eat of His fruit.{1} And their hands have not produced it,{2} so will they not be grateful?",footnotes:1:[i.e., that which Allāh has produced for them.],footnotes:2:[An alternative meaning is \"And [eat from] what their hands have produced [i.e., planted and harvested].\"  Both are grammatically correct.]
  36,36,"Exalted is He who created all pairs{1} - from what the earth grows and from themselves and from that which they do not know.",footnotes:1:[Or "all species."]
  37,19,"It will be only one shout, and at once they will be observing."
  37,20,"They will say, "
  37,21,"[They will be told], "
